  Simplification</a></font></div>
  <div id=PPTC22 class=CTxt style='display:none'><font size=2>
  <ul>
   <li>Approach #1</li>
   <ul>
    <li>Simplified F' <span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>†</span>in the form of sum
        of products</li>
    <li>Apply DeMorgan's theorem F = (F')'</li>
    <li>F': sum of products &#8594; F: product of sums</li>
   </ul>
   <li>Approach #2: duality</li>
   <ul>
    <li>Combinations of maxterms (it was minterms)</li>
    <li>M<sub>0</sub>M<sub>1</sub> = (A+B+C+D)(A+B+C+D') = (A+B+C)+(DD') = A+B+C</li>
   </ul>
   <br>
  </ul>
  </font></div>
  </td>
