 <tr onmouseover="Over(this)" onmouseout="Out(this)" onclick="Follow(this)"
  style='cursor:hand'>
  <td align=right valign=top>
  <div class=sldNum><font size=2>33</font></div>
  </td>
  <td>
  <div id=PPTP33 class=PTxt><font size=2><a
  href="javascript:GoToSld('slide0033.htm');" id=PPTL33>Procedure with Two
  Levels NAND</a></font></div>
  <div id=PPTC33 class=CTxt style='display:none'><font size=2>
  <ul>
   <li>The procedure</li>
   <ul>
    <li>Simplified in the form of sum of products;</li>
    <li>A NAND gate for each product term; the inputs to each NAND gate are the
        literals of the term (the first level);</li>
    <li>A single NAND gate for the second sum term (the second level);</li>
    <li>A term with a single literal requires an inverter in the first level.</li>
   </ul>
  </ul>
  </font></div>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr onmouseover="Over(this)" onmouseout="Out(this)" onclick="Follow(this)"
  style='cursor:hand'>
  <td align=right valign=top>
  <div class=sldNum><font size=2>34</font></div>
  </td>
  <td>
  <div id=PPTP34 class=PTxt><font size=2><a
  href="javascript:GoToSld('slide0034.htm');" id=PPTL34>Multilevel NAND
  Circuits</a></font></div>
  <div id=PPTC34 class=CTxt style='display:none'><font size=2>
  <ul>
   <li>Boolean function implementation</li>
   <ul>
    <li>AND-OR logic &#8594; NAND-NAND logic</li>
    <ul>
     <li>AND &#8594; AND + inverter</li>
     <li>OR: inverter + OR = NAND</li>
     <li>For every bubble that is not compensated by another small circle along
         the same line, insert an inverter.</li>
    </ul>
   </ul>
   <br>
  </ul>
  </font></div>
  </td>
 </tr>
